{
  "texts": [
    "To ensure fair comparisons, we categorized DUD-E targets into three groups on the basis of their sequency identity with the properties for generated molecules, including count (a), molecular weight (b), minimum in-place GlideSP score (c), GlideSP redocking score (d) and r.m.s.d.",
    "versus low-energy conformer (e).",
    "These distributions are depicted along SAS and QED.",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s42256-023-00775-6",
    "Pocket2Mol training targets: severe (more than 90%), moderate (30-90%) and limited (less than 30%) information leakage."
  ]
}